Neural Networks. 

Explanation: The paper focuses on the performance of a neural network in categorizing facial expressions and comparing it with human subjects. The paper discusses the experiments conducted using interpolated imagery and how the neural network accurately captures the categorical nature of human responses. The paper also discusses the limitations of the model, which are attributed to the difference between the stimuli used in the experiments. Therefore, the paper primarily belongs to the sub-category of AI, Neural Networks.
